# ============================================================
# KinderOS — Cursor AI Rules
# Multi-tenant SaaS for Kindergarten Schools (India)
# ============================================================
# This file governs ALL code generation in this project.
# Never deviate from these conventions.

## PROJECT IDENTITY
You are building KinderOS — a multi-tenant B2B SaaS platform for
kindergarten schools in India. Each school is an isolated tenant.
The product has 5 portals: Owner Dashboard, Teacher Dashboard,
Admin Staff Portal, Parent Mobile App, and School Public Website.
There is also a Super Admin panel for platform management.

## TECH STACK — NEVER DEVIATE
- Framework:     Next.js 14 App Router (TypeScript, strict mode)
- Database:      Supabase (PostgreSQL) with Row Level Security
- ORM:           Prisma 5.x
- Auth:          Clerk (org-level multi-tenancy — each school = 1 Clerk org)
- Styling:       Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- Payments:      Razorpay (fee collection, payment links, webhooks)
- Messaging:     Twilio (WhatsApp Business API + SMS)
- File Storage:  Cloudflare R2 (photos, documents, receipts)
- Email:         Resend
- AI:            Anthropic Claude API (progress report generation, smart alerts)
- PDF:           react-pdf / puppeteer (fee receipts, reports)
- Push notif:    Firebase Cloud Messaging
- Deployment:    Vercel (preview per PR, prod on main)

## MONOREPO STRUCTURE
```
kinderos/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/          # Next.js app — all portals + public pages
│   └── mobile/       # React Native (Expo) — Parent app (Phase 2)
├── packages/
│   ├── db/           # Prisma schema + generated client
│   ├── ui/           # Shared shadcn/ui components
│   ├── config/       # Shared ESLint, TS, Tailwind config
│   └── utils/        # Shared helpers (formatters, validators)
├── .cursorrules
├── package.json      # pnpm workspace root
└── turbo.json
```

